{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/10-steps-to-become-a-data-scientist-6c8e7ac6288e", "time": 1683002155.4920802, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/10-steps-to-become-a-data-scientist-6c8e7ac6288e/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "10 steps to become a Data Scientist | by Przemek Chojecki | Towards Data Science", "h1": "10 steps to become a Data Scientist", "description": "It\u2019s not always easy to become a data scientist, even for the best of engineers. However, it\u2019s not too difficult for any student and there are a few things you should know beforehand. This article\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/practical-guide-to-become-a-data-scientist-2483a5f83770", "anchor_text": "succeed in data science", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/data-science-books-you-should-read-in-2020-358f70e1d9b2", "anchor_text": "become a great data scientist.", "paragraph_index": 19}, {"url": "https://amzn.to/3aQVTjs", "anchor_text": "Data Science Job: How to become a Data Scientist", "paragraph_index": 20}], "all_paragraphs": ["It\u2019s not always easy to become a data scientist, even for the best of engineers. However, it\u2019s not too difficult for any student and there are a few things you should know beforehand. This article takes a look at them, providing you a clear road map to succeed in data science.", "For every question, write the problem statement in plain English. I have already written a post about making readable data science problems.", "This is also a good time to take a look at some technical examples of the problems that real companies encounter with the data science process.", "Make your code and run it. The interviewers will take a look at the code and answer the questions afterwards (see below).", "Make sure to have valid solutions that are both concise and creative.", "Write down your responses to the questions.", "Refine your answers, ask yourself why you didn\u2019t make use of some existing frameworks or tools", "This will help you to identify areas that you need to learn more about, and convince yourself to write up some material for future interviews.", "As a bonus, prepare and show your solution to a third party who will help you get in touch with the organization that interviews candidates", "Prepare a notebook with all of your solutions so you can discuss your solutions with your team", "Define the assumptions you think your interviewer has in the company and the tasks that you will be dealing with. Do not compromise on these assumptions as it\u2019s a good way to separate yourself from the crowd", "Identify the solution that meets your team\u2019s expectations and tasks. Review your team\u2019s expectations and tools when you have time.", "Use the law of Pareto\u2019s distribution, a concept in statistics. In that case, the distribution describes the most probable outcome that the best of any pair of independent events would give. Consider the following values as a sample of the data.", "Every question has a possible answer that fits the data you have. Invest your time in defining a robust solution, applying it, and prove it in a future interview", "The experience in programming is crucial for data science: You will have to execute the code and find bugs without any code. In that case, no code is worse than no code. If you are asked to re-write the code and fix bugs, you can try with a data scientist.", "Differences in programming languages are less important than differences in culture. A learning curve for both groups can help you to identify where you need to stick to have your best chances.", "If you are nervous, you can also ask questions in the interview about how to structure your code to fit with the structure of the company, and how to track what work you need to do for the upcoming weeks.", "Every company values data science; it is highly unlikely that they will hire someone who doesn\u2019t have sufficient skills. This can be a negative point in case you go into the company already believing that you are the best data scientist for that company.", "It\u2019s worth bearing in mind, however, that some teams don\u2019t really care about and or find great candidates. As a data scientist, you will have to negotiate your salary, work hours, and many other things during the interview process.", "It takes a long time to become an engineer; a shorter amount of time to become a great data scientist.", "Finally, if you want to have an overview of what it means to be a Data Scientist, then have a look at my book Data Science Job: How to become a Data Scientist which will guide you through the process.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "AI & crypto, PhD in mathematics, Forbes 30 under 30, former Oxford fellow."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F6c8e7ac6288e&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2F10-steps-to-become-a-data-scientist-6c8e7ac6288e&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2F10-steps-to-become-a-data-scientist-6c8e7ac6288e&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "http